The State Board may remove a member of the county board for:
Immorality;
Misconduct in office;
Incompetency; or
Willful neglect of duty.

The Commission shall consist of the following six voting members:
One member appointed by the Senator members of the Washington County Delegation;
One member appointed by the Delegate members of the Washington County Delegation;
One member appointed by the county board; and
The following three members appointed by the County Commissioners:
One member representing the Washington County business community;
One member representing the Washington County Citizens Advisory Council; and
One member representing the Washington County educational community.
